Zod allows string validation with methods like email(), min(), max(), and url().

```ts
const schema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email(),
  name: z.string().min(2).max(100),
});

const result = schema.safeParse(data);
if (!result.success) {
  console.error(result.error.format());
}
```

Key methods:
- z.string().email() - validates email format
- z.string().min(n) - minimum length
- z.string().max(n) - maximum length
- schema.safeParse(data) - validates without throwing
- schema.parse(data) - validates and throws on failure
